HEADWORD: Acyl
<hw>Ac"yl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ac</ets>id +
<ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Org. Chem.)</fld> <def>An acid radical, as
acetyl, malonyl, or benzoyl. An acyl radical can be depicted as
<chform>R-CO-</chform>, where <chform>-CO-</chform> is the carbonyl
group, and R is the group that characterizes the acyl moiety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

